1. Explain linux file permissions
A: read - r - 4
   write - w - 2
   execte - x - 1
   Owner -- group -- others

2. Diff between 755, 644,777
A: 755 --> rwx--rx-rx
   644 --> rw--r--r
   777 --> rwx--rwx--rwx ( we never use 777 in production unless its really necessary)

3. Diff between chmod,chown, chgrp
A: chmod --> changes file permissions --> chmod 755 file_name
   chown --> changes file owner --> chown ubuntu file.txt
   chgrp --> changes file group --> chgrp developers file.txt

4. Express symbolic and numeric permissions
A: numeric : chmod 744 file.txt
   symbolic: chmod u+x app.sh ( gives owner execute permission)
             chmod g-w app.sh ( remove write permission from group)
          u --> user/owner | g --> group | o --> others

5. How do you recursively change permissions
A: chmod -R 755 file.txt

6. Diff between file and directory permissions
A: Files:
    read --> view contents
    write --> modifies the file
    execute --> run the file
  Directories:
    read --> list files
    write --> create / delete files
    execute --> enter directory (cd)

7. How to create a new user, how to add a user to group
A: to create user: sudo adduser aishu
   to add user to group: sudo usermod -aG group1 aishu
    verify : groups aishu ( tells aishu user is in which groups)

8. How to lock and unlock a user?
A: to immediately disable access for user we lock them, when we lock a ! is added to the password by linux so when user tries to login it shows password error so
    they cant login
   sudo passwd -l aishu --> lock username
   sudo passwd -u aishu --> unlocks username

9. check who is currently logged in
A: who OR w OR last

